track.name: Vegas (From the Original Motion Picture Soundtrack ELVIS)

album.title: Vegas (From the Original Motion Picture Soundtrack ELVIS)

wiki.summary: "Vegas" is a song by Doja Cat, released as the lead single from the soundtrack for Baz Luhrmann's Elvis Presley biopic Elvis on May 6, 2022. It was produced by Yeti Beats and Rogét Chahayed. The song interpolates a sample of Big Mama Thornton's 1952 song "Hound Dog", which was written by Jerry Leiber and Mike Stoller and notably covered by Presley. The song's lyrics refer to a man who was an "underwhelming lover" whom Doja Cat feels "never deserved her attention". Read more on Last.fm.
